        <div class="card card-2">
            <div class="container">
                <img src="Glass Waste.jpg" alt="">
            </div>
            <div class="details">
                <h3>Glass Waste</h3>
                <p>Some countries have developed special methods for recycling glass waste. For example, in Sweden, glass waste is melted to generate heat energy, which is used to heat cities or generate electricity. This method not only ensures the disposal of glass waste but also contributes to the production of renewable energy.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card card-3">
            <div class="container">
                <img src="Organic Waste.jpg" alt="">
            </div>
            <div class="details">
                <h3>Organic Waste</h3>
                <p>The organic wastes obtained are converted into methane gas (biogas) by bacteria through anaerobic fermentation process, turning it into an energy source containing 50% to 75% methane. While this method prevents organic waste from harming the environment, it contributes to the reduction of fossil fuel use and the prevention of approximately 20 million tons of CO2 emissions by producing approximately 2 billion cubic meters of biogas per year.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
